{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7NpsMTM2EF1K79QWby","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. The tests pass.\n\n**The bug:** `orderTotalCents` rounded each line's discounted amount separately and then summed them. The spec (documented right above the function) requires summing the subtotal exactly, applying the discount to that subtotal, and rounding **once**. Per-line rounding accumulates drift — e.g. two lines that individually round *up* can push a true $8.99 total to $9.00.\n\n**The fix** (`src/money.js`): sum the exact integer subtotal first, then apply the discount and round a single time. `invoice.js` and `report.js` both call through this function, so billing and checkout now agree."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":314,"cache_read_input_tokens":23561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":314},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84c5e2fa-4176-4cf7-af24-beffb14c4f51","uuid":"4045413c-e51d-422a-9894-bf122af70a0b","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:39:45.852Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7NoXV5bdj2Cjwd99hM"}
